@@ -0,0 +1,33 @@
+//! The **custodian** crate (L4) — the zone's background durability-maintenance
+//! plane (proposal 0005, Milestone 3). A storage system written by M2 can store
+//! erasure-coded data but cannot yet *keep* it: a D server that dies after a clean
+//! commit silently lowers a chunk's redundancy and nothing notices. The custodian
+//! is the plane that garbage-collects, scrubs, reconstructs, rebalances, and emits
+//! the durability telemetry that makes the guarantee observable.
+//!
+//! This crate is the **foundation skeleton** (M3.3, proposal 0005 PR-sequence step
+//! 3): the scaffold the four maintenance loops (GC, scrub, reconstruction,
+//! rebalance — slices 4–7) layer on rather than re-invent. It stands up:
+//!
+//! - [`leadership`] — a **single active custodian per zone**, leader-elected and
+//!   **fenced** via the existing [`wyrd_traits::Coordination::elect_leader`]; a
+//!   deposed-but-running custodian's action is rejected by its stale fencing token.
+//! - [`selector`] — the zone-local **failure-domain-aware placement selector**
+//!   (re-exported from [`wyrd_core::placement`], the shared home so the write
+//!   fan-out and custodian re-placement use one primitive).
+//! - [`reconcile`] — the **reconciliation control-loop skeleton** (a fenced tick).
+//! - [`telemetry`] — the **backend-agnostic OpenTelemetry seam** (ADR-0012): a
+//!   first custodian metric is emitted through an exporter that names no concrete
+//!   backend, so every later loop emits from its first commit (ADR-0011).
+//!
+//! Dependency rule (ADR-0010): this crate depends only on `traits`, `core`, and
+//! `tracing` — **never** a concrete backend. The four loops' *behaviour*, the
+//! version-conditional repair location-update, and the full DST campaign are out
+//! of scope for this slice (proposal 0005 slices 4–8).
+
+#![forbid(unsafe_code)]
+
+pub mod leadership;
+pub mod reconcile;
+pub mod selector;
+pub mod telemetry;
